Phase 5b / L-discipline-2 — end-to-end semantic-discharge proof
for Phase 5 Slice A's StreamCorec lowering.

The recursion-design doc named end-to-end discharge proofs as
"the strongest pin" for Slice A but didn't land them initially.
This test (and its sibling test_lean_recursion_stream_fibs_proof
when it lands) closes that gap.

What it pins: a textual subset assertion in smoketest plus
`lake env lean` typing — exactly the L-16-lesson standard the
project pays attention to — only catches gross structural
breakage. A semantic-discharge proof catches meaning-preservation
regressions: if the `lookup` substitution were dropped, or the
`Stream.rec` iota were misrouted, or `mkStreamFix`'s structural
recursion were reordered, the proofs here would fail.

What's proved:
- streamIdx Bool RecOnes.allTrue 0 = Bool.true (base case; doesn't
  exercise the recursion proper, but pins the seed-handling).
- streamIdx Bool RecOnes.allTrue 1 = Bool.true (actually exercises
  the lookup_ → Stream.rec iota → previous-element retrieval).

Both rely on three axioms in CryptolToLean.SAWCorePrelude_proofs:
gen_atWithDefault, atWithDefault_out_of_bounds (existing), and
atWithDefault_singleton_zero (new, Phase 5b/L-discipline-2). The
last is a Phase 8 candidate — when atWithDefault becomes a
structural def, the axiom promotes to a theorem.

Compare offline_proof_t1 / t3 / t4: those exercise bv-arithmetic
+ ite chains. This test exercises stream corecursion + recursive
lookup substitution — orthogonal coverage.
